<App layout="vertical-sticky" var.recording="{false}">
  <DataSource id="enhanceStatus" url="/__enhance/status" />

  <AppHeader>
    <Text fontWeight="bold">Tools</Text>
    <Theme paddingHorizontal-Button-sm="$space-1">
      <HStack gap="$space-0_5">
        <Button
          label="A−"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Decrease app font size"
          onClick="window.setAppFontSize(window.getAppFontSize() - 1)" />
        <Button
          label="A+"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Increase app font size"
          onClick="window.setAppFontSize(window.getAppFontSize() + 1)" />
        <Button
          label="{recording ? '⏹ stop' : '🎤 voice'}"
          variant="ghost"
          tooltip="Voice input — click to start, click again to send"
          onClick="recording ? (recording = false, voiceStop(t => { if (t) toTurn('voice: ' + t); })) : (voiceStart(), navigate('/talk'), recording = true)" />
      </HStack>
    </Theme>
  </AppHeader>

  <NavPanel>
    <NavLink label="Talk" to="/talk" />
    <NavLink label="Worklist" to="/" exact="true" />
    <NavLink label="Commits" to="/commits" />
    <NavLink label="Sessions" to="/sessions" />
    <NavLink label="README" to="/readme" />
  </NavPanel>

  <VStack
    when="{enhanceStatus.value && !enhanceStatus.value.enhanced}"
    padding="$space-4"
    gap="$space-3"
    backgroundColor="$color-info-50"
    borderBottom="1px solid $color-info-200">
    <Heading level="h3">Configure agent coordination</Heading>
    <Markdown content="The agent tools drawer hosts these views, all driven by data the agent produces or your interaction with it. The header at the top is pinned, so the 🎤 voice toggle and font-size controls stay reachable from any tab.

- **Talk** — live transcript of the current session, with alternating user / assistant turns and a spinner that shows while you wait for a reply. Click 🎤 voice in the AppHeader to dictate from any tab; clicking it again sends the transcript as a fresh user turn. Yes / No / Esc buttons in Talk's own sticky header send one-click replies.
- **Worklist** — renders `resources/proposal.json` as a checklist of pending items the agent has proposed. You triage with checkboxes; *Approve selected* and *Drop selected* round-trip the result back to the agent as a fresh user turn (via the `toTurn` shell helper). Optional feedback typed in the box rides along with the action.
- **Commits** — recent commits, with one-click push to origin when you are ahead.
- **Sessions** — browse and search past agent sessions for this project. Claude Code and Codex histories are auto-detected from local transcripts.
- **README** — this project's README rendered for quick reference.

Setting up writes:
- `.claude/xmlui-desktop-conventions.md` — the conventions sidecar (worklist schema and lifecycle, helper APIs, charting via `EChart`, what belongs in the right pane).
- An `@`-import line in `CLAUDE.md` (created if missing, appended idempotently if present) so every new Claude Code session in this project pulls those conventions in automatically.

What setup deliberately does **not** do:

- Create `resources/proposal.json`. The Worklist tab works without it — when the file is missing, the route serves an empty default and the worklist shows *(none)*. The agent writes to the file the first time it proposes items.
- Inject `&lt;script src=&quot;/__shell/helpers.js&quot;&gt;` into your `index.html`. That script is only needed if your own xmlui markup wants to call `toShell`/`toTurn`/`openExternal`/`logToHost` (e.g., a custom Approve button you wire). The drawer's tabs work either way." />
    <Text fontSize="$fontSize-sm" color="$textColor-secondary">
      Existing Claude Code sessions in this project need /clear or restart
      to pick up the new CLAUDE.md.
    </Text>
    <HStack>
      <Button
        label="Set up"
        onClick="window.fetch('/__enhance/run').then(() => enhanceStatus.refetch())" />
    </HStack>
  </VStack>

  <Pages fallbackPath="/">
    <Page url="/"><Workspace /></Page>
    <Page url="/talk"><Talk /></Page>
    <Page url="/sessions"><Sessions /></Page>
    <Page url="/commits"><Commits /></Page>
    <Page url="/readme"><Readme /></Page>
  </Pages>
</App>
